Package ml.dmlc.xgboost4j.java.example

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicWalkThrough
    a simple example of java wrapper for xgboost
    BoostFromPrediction
    example for start from a initial base prediction
    CrossValidation
    an example of cross validation
    CustomObjective
    an example user define objective and eval NOTE: when you do customized loss function, the default prediction value is margin this may make buildin evalution metric not function properly for example, we are doing logistic loss, the prediction is score before logistic transformation he buildin evaluation error assumes input is after logistic transformation Take this in mind when you use the customization, and maybe you need write customized evaluation function
    CustomObjective.EvalError
    user defined eval function.
    CustomObjective.LogRegObj
    loglikelihoode loss obj function
    ExternalMemory
    simple example for using external memory version
    GeneralizedLinearModel
    this is an example of fit generalized linear model in xgboost basically, we are using linear model, instead of tree for our boosters
    PredictFirstNtree
    predict first ntree
    PredictLeafIndices
    predict leaf indices
